  "prompt": "What are the top ten PC games ever?",
  "response": "The list of the top ten PC games ever can vary depending on personal preferences, genres, and the criteria used (e.g., popularity, critical acclaim, cultural impact, or sales). However, here\u2019s a widely agreed-upon list of iconic and influential PC games that have stood the test of time:\n\n1. **The Elder Scrolls V: Skyrim** (2011)  \n   - An open-world RPG that set a new standard for exploration, modding, and player freedom.\n\n2. **Minecraft** (2011)  \n   - A sandbox game that revolutionized creativity and has become one of the best-selling games of all time.\n\n3. **World of Warcraft** (2004)  \n   - The most iconic MMORPG, shaping the genre and maintaining a massive player base for over a decade.\n\n4. **Half-Life 2** (2004)  \n   - A groundbreaking first-person shooter with a compelling story, physics-based gameplay, and excellent level design.\n\n5. **The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt** (2015)  \n   - Widely regarded as one of the best RPGs ever, with a rich narrative, expansive world, and memorable characters.\n\n6. **Doom** (1993)  \n   - The game that popularized the first-person shooter genre and revolutionized PC gaming in the 1990s.\n\n7. **StarCraft** (1998)  \n   - A legendary real-time strategy game that became a cornerstone of esports, especially in South Korea.\n\n8. **Portal 2** (2011)  \n   - A critically acclaimed puzzle-platformer with innovative mechanics, humor, and a memorable story.\n\n9. **Counter-Strike: Global Offensive (CS:GO)** (2012)  \n   - A defining multiplayer shooter that has remained a staple in competitive gaming.\n\n10. **Diablo II** (2000)  \n   - A classic action RPG that set the standard for loot-driven gameplay and dungeon crawling.\n\nHonorable mentions include **Baldur\u2019s Gate II**, **Civilization V**, **Mass Effect 2**, **League of Legends**, and **Dark Souls**, all of which have had significant impacts on gaming culture and design.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
